# Workflow Heading Pattern for Interactive Workflows

## Purpose
Ensure all interactive workflows and menu actions provide clear context and navigation by printing Mocha-styled headings before input/output prompts and before progress bars or long-running operations.

## Core Principles
- Print a heading before input/output prompts (e.g., "Input/Output Selection").
- Print a heading before progress bars or long-running operations (e.g., "Progress").
- Use `print_header` or `print_section` from `dataset_forge.utils.printing`.
- Use the Catppuccin Mocha color scheme (`dataset_forge.utils.color.Mocha`).
- Headings must clearly indicate the workflow and stage.

## Best Practices
- Add headings to all new and refactored workflows.
- Review all menu actions for compliance before merging.
- Reference the Style Guide for rationale and code examples.

## Example
```python
from dataset_forge.utils.printing import print_header, print_section
from dataset_forge.utils.color import Mocha

print_header("ðŸ§© Best Tile Extraction (PepeDP) - Input/Output Selection", color=Mocha.pink)
# ... input prompts ...
print_section("Best Tile Extraction Progress", color=Mocha.pink)
# ... run progress bar ...
```

## Review Checklist
- [ ] Heading before input/output prompts
- [ ] Heading before progress bars/long-running operations
- [ ] Uses Catppuccin Mocha color scheme and centralized printing utilities
- [ ] All menu actions and workflows reviewed for this pattern

